  <abstract>An excerpt from an oral history interview with Nashville investor John S. Bransford, Sr., conducted on 9 July 1980 by Leanne Thornton as part of the Historic Nashville, Inc. 1910-1935 Oral History Project. Bransford reads a letter he wrote describing his parents' decision not to purchase Belle Meade Mansion in 1910 or 1911 because of the tragedies that had befallen the family that owned it. Later, Bransford married the owner's daughter, Helen Dickinson The complete interview, as well an index, is available in the Special Collections Division.</abstract>
